JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s power utility Eskom on Friday said it regretted but understood a decision by Chief Executive Brian Molefe to step down and clear his name after he was implicated in a report by the anti-graft watchdog on allegations of influence peddling.&#8220;The decision taken by Mr Molefe was regrettable but understandable,&#8221; board chairman Baldwin Ngubane said in a statement.